sentence: Looking at options trading activity among components of the S&P 500 index, there is noteworthy activity today in Home Depot Inc (Symbol: HD), where a total volume of 69,619 contracts has been traded thus far today, a contract volume which is representative of approximately 7.0 million underlying shares (given that every 1 contract represents 100 underlying shares).
That number works out to 208.8% of HD's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 3.3 million shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $220 strike put option expiring November 22, 2019, with 3,943 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 394,300 underlying shares of HD.
